Avantika SeethWomen who make a difference in South Africa deserve to be recognised Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The Businesswomen&rsquo;s Association of SA&rsquo;s 2017 Businesswoman of the Year Awards organisers announced the 13 finalists at a luncheon held at the new Sasol head office in Sandton on Wednesday afternoon.The 2015 Businesswoman of the Year in the government category, Tembela Kulu, said: &ldquo;We should not be modest. When we introduce each other as women, we must do it boldly.&rdquo;This year&rsquo;s winning categories will recognise participants involved in social entrepreneurship, the corporate environment, education and entrepreneurship on September 6 at the Sandton Convention Centre. The nonprofit&rsquo;s president, Farzanah Mall, said this year&rsquo;s theme &ndash; Women with No Filter &ndash; was chosen to help focus the spotlight on women&rsquo;s &ldquo;internal and external light&rdquo;. &ldquo;It doesn&rsquo;t matter who we are or where we come from, we all have this light that shines through us, and this is what we need to focus on as women,&rdquo; she said.Italian artist Fabiana Vizzani Reis donated a painting reflecting the femininity, power and light of women, which will be auctioned on the night of the awards.&ldquo;We are hoping to get in some offers before the night of the awards, so please spread the word,&rdquo; Mall said, while guests tucked into a classy buffet-style lunch of sweet potato bake, curried fish pie and sirloin steaks, with a fresh green salad and stir-fried vegetables. The delectable offering of desserts included raspberry tartlets, mini carrot cakes and chocolate brownies to sweeten the palate24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.